con:soapui-project.name: CONNECTDirectConfig
con:soapui-project.con:description:
This project tests the various services that make up the Direct ConfigurationService. While no-op and dependency issues are being worked out, all TestSuites (and the contained TestCases) must be run in the order provided. Also, tests should be run against a clean configdb until discrepancies are resolved with services that (unsuccessfully) attempt to control the primary key when inserting a new record.
Note: At the moment, DNS and CertPolicy TestSuites are disabled due to the no-op implementation deployed in CONNECTDirectConfig.

con:testSuite.name: CertificateService
con:testSuite.con:description: Refer to the Project Description for information on running this TestSuite, or each TestCase Description for information on that particular service.

con:testCase.name: addCertificates
con:testCase.con:description: This will add two entries for Certificate, so we can test getting more than one cert later in this TestSuite.

con:testCase.name: removeCertificates
con:testCase.con:description: This will delete all certificates belonging to a specific owner; the response is the same whether or not any certificates were removed.

con:testCase.name: removeCertificatesForOwner
con:testCase.con:description: This will delete all certificates belonging to a specific owner; the response is the same whether or not any certificates were removed.

con:testSuite.name: SettingService
con:testSuite.con:description: Refer to the Project Description for information on running this TestSuite, or each TestCase Description for information on that particular service.

con:testCase.name: addSetting
con:testCase.con:description: This will add two unique values for Setting, so we can test getting more than one setting later in this TestSuite.

con:testCase.name: getAllSettings
con:testCase.con:description: This will retrieve all values for Setting and verify that at least one value was returned (since we just added values)

con:testCase.name: getSettingByName
con:testCase.con:description: This will retrieve a specific Setting that was added previously and verify that it contains the correct value.

con:testCase.name: updateSetting
con:testCase.con:description: This will update a value and then retrieve it again for verification.
